PHILIPPINE REFINING CORPORATION, Proctor & Gamble, and American Linseed Company, Libelants-Appellees, v. UNITED STATES of America, Respondent-Appellant. No. 324. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. May 19, 1930. Charles H. Tuttle, U. S. Atty., of New York City (William E. Collins, Sp. Asst. U. S. Atty., of New York City, of counsel), for appellant. Bigham, Englar, Jones & Houston, of New York City (D. Roger Englar and James N. Seneeal, both of New York City, of counsel), for appellees.

Before-MANTON, SWAN, and AUGUSTUS N. HAND, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Decree [29 F.(2d) 134, 33 F.(2d) 974] affirmed.
